The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Anand appeal 

New Delhi: World No. 2 Viswanathan Anand said the need of the hour is to have an unified world chess championship which will pit the best players against each other. 

?We now have different world chess events and the sport is getting hurt with the top players not taking on each other in a unified world chess championship,? Anand said here on Friday. (PTI) 

